# Copperhead build-time configuration.
# Copy to .env (gitignored). Every variable here is OPTIONAL — the site
# builds and deploys with no environment at all (the Strapi 5 public role
# allows tokenless reads, and the manager-annotation dev-preview tool ships
# with a committed publishable Supabase key). Set these only to override a
# default per environment, e.g. in the Netlify env UI.

# Optional read-only Strapi API token. Attached server-side only; never
# reaches the browser. Set the same variable in Netlify UI (and CI secrets)
# if the CMS public role is ever locked down.
NUXT_STRAPI_TOKEN=

# Optional override of the CMS origin (defaults to the production Strapi 5).
NUXT_PUBLIC_STRAPI_URL=https://v2.hub.icjia-api.cloud

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Manager annotations (dev-preview tool) — Supabase
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# The review-annotation feature stores comment threads in Supabase. The
# defaults are ALREADY committed in hub.config.mjs and ship in the build, so
# NO Netlify environment variable is required — annotations work out of the
# box. The key below is a *publishable* key: it is safe in the client bundle
# because Row Level Security is the real boundary. It is NOT a secret.
#
# Set these two ONLY to point the tool at a different Supabase project without
# editing code. On Netlify: Site configuration → Environment variables → add
# them, then redeploy. Because they are NUXT_PUBLIC_*, they are baked into the
# build and exposed to the browser (correct for a publishable key).
#
# Where to find the values — Supabase dashboard → your project → Settings:
#   • NUXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL — Settings → API → "Project URL"
#       (looks like https://<project-ref>.supabase.co)
#   • NUXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_KEY — Settings → API Keys → the "publishable" key
#       (starts with "sb_publishable_"; the anon / public-safe key).
#       NEVER use the "secret" / service_role key here — it must never reach
#       the browser.
#
# The table name (copperhead_annotations) is a fixed code constant in
# hub.config.mjs and is not overridable by env. When the kill switch is off
# (hub.annotations.enabled = false) these values are stripped from the build,
# so no override is needed at go-live — see the README runbook.
NUXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://efgevsdftkrancswojcz.supabase.co
NUXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_KEY=sb_publishable_xYEjTCTxp-UaYGsFQMay6g_HA7BM9cn
